<br>
All we are is more extreme at the same things they are.  The difference is we have larger brains and can bind time perspective more accurately. Why did this happen?  In part because we started eating meat at some point in our history.  The meat protiens enabled us to develop larger brains.  We have opposable thumbs so we can create and use dynamic tool sets.  We are land creatures so we have use of fire and energy consumption work systems that water creatures do not.  We developed a communication skill that enabled us to pass on more than just emulative learning schema.  We are pattern seeking, story telling creatures.  Then again, so are most mammals, just to a lesser degree than we are. <p>DBC67<br>
